2020.Agency: MINISTRY OF CULTURE, COMMUNITY AND YOUTH (MCCY)
2020.Blurb: MCCY's overall PSXI score recorded a significant growth since 2019. This is mainly due to improvements in the Interactions score.

MINDEF saw a slight increase in its overall PSXI score since 2019. While its Impressions score has remained constant since 2019, its Interactions score improved significantly. It scores relatively lower among Seniors than for other age groups.

MOE's overall PSXI score recorded an important increase since 2019. This can be attributed to a significant increase in the Interactions score. It scored relatively higher among PMETs and middle-age citizens.
MOH recorded an important increase in its overall PSXI score between 2019 and 2020. While its Interactions score increased slightly, there was a significant increase in the Sentiments score.
MHA's overall PSXI score slightly increased since 2019. Middle-aged and non-PMET citizens scored it relatively lower than other groups.
MOM's overall PSXI score has remained virtually unchanged. Its score for Seniors was the lowest across age groups.
MND overall PSXI did not change much since 2019. While its Interactions score is low, middle-aged citizens scored it relatively higher than other age groups.

2020.Agency: MINISTRY OF SOCIAL AND FAMILY DEVELOPMENT (MSF)
2020.Blurb: MSF's overall PSXI score saw a significant improvement since 2019, mainly driven by the Interactions score. Among all age groups, Youth gave it the highest score.

HPB is very far along its digitalisation journey, though its 2020 score is lower than in 2019 (76.0).

The PSXI score for SportSG slightly improved from 2019. This was mainly driven by an increase in the Interactions score.

ACRA's overall PSXI score saw a 15.7-point increase since 2019. This is mainly driven by a significant increase in its Interactions score.
